summary: Pokemon Card of the Day Schedule: Call of Legends
title: Pokemon Card of the Day Schedule: Call of Legends
body:
Call of Legends was a filler set that was meant to bridge the gap between the main HeartGold & SoulSilver sets and the international release of Black & White. Games didn’t release simultaneously across the world back then, so a delay set was the norm at the end of a generation. The set was mostly reprints of cards from the previous 4 sets, which will not be covered again due to the small time between prints. There were a few new ones, though, and 10 of these cards will be reviewed here. The big one was the much-anticipated Lost World, a card that, along with Gengar Prime, dominated Japan for a while. The format elsewhere was very different, however, and it wasn’t dominant, but it was still a good card just like a few of the others in the set.

1460: Lucario
1461: Pachirisu
1462: Mr. Mime
1463: Tangrowth
1464: Mime Jr.
1465: Seviper
1466: Relicanth
1467: Lost Remover
1468: Lost World
1469: Research Record

blog.name: friendsafariserver
blog.title: Friend Safari!
blog.description:
Friend Safari is a SFW, OC-friendly, paragraph-style roleplay server for main series Pokémon games. From Kanto to Alola, the whole Pokémon world is your Cloyster! Members of this server are allowed a total of four played characters, with at least one required to be canonical.

The server is run by a team of five mods who you can learn more about via the mods page. We cultivate an easygoing and open atmosphere, with member comfort and happiness being our top priority.

All of the links are in the drop down menu under Rowlet, labeled Pokémon! Hovering over each Pokémon will tell you what page they link to!
